1
00:00:04,504 --> 00:00:06,138
<i>In 2026,</i>

2
00:00:06,139 --> 00:00:09,541
<i>I announced a bank acquisition
and entry into AI,</i>

3
00:00:09,542 --> 00:00:13,312
<i>earning me the title
of the Reiwa era's charismatic leader.</i>

4
00:00:13,313 --> 00:00:14,748
<i>I, Kosei Neo, president of NEOXIS,</i>

5
00:00:15,415 --> 00:00:17,716
<i>was pushed from behind by someone</i>

6
00:00:17,717 --> 00:00:19,953
<i>and should have died.</i>

7
00:00:21,021 --> 00:00:23,222
<i>Yet I woke up in the body of Eito Nomoto,</i>

8
00:00:23,223 --> 00:00:25,491
<i>who had also died in a separate accident</i>

9
00:00:25,492 --> 00:00:27,426
<i>and looked exactly like me.</i>

10
00:00:27,427 --> 00:00:30,396
<i>Eito was the son of Eiji Nomoto,</i>

11
00:00:30,397 --> 00:00:32,197
<i>the man I'd dragged into that fall.</i>

12
00:00:32,198 --> 00:00:32,931
‎DECEMBER 27, 2012

13
00:00:32,932 --> 00:00:35,035
<i>The year was 2012.</i>

14
00:00:35,935 --> 00:00:38,237
<i>To fight back against Soman,</i>

15
00:00:38,238 --> 00:00:40,639
<i>Ichimanda's supermarket,</i>

16
00:00:40,640 --> 00:00:42,574
<i>I revived the Akari Shopping Street</i>

17
00:00:42,575 --> 00:00:45,544
<i>that I had once forced out, only to face…</i>

18
00:00:45,545 --> 00:00:48,313
The debt is exactly 10 million yen.

19
00:00:48,314 --> 00:00:51,550
<i>The hardships of living as Eito.</i>

20
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:52,519
What thing?

21
00:00:53,186 --> 00:00:55,187
<i>I really am living</i>

22
00:00:55,188 --> 00:00:58,358
<i>inside Eito Nomoto's body.</i>

23
00:00:59,826 --> 00:01:02,529
<i>But… the real me…</i>

24
00:01:03,463 --> 00:01:07,132
<i>I should be able to find whoever killed</i>

25
00:01:07,133 --> 00:01:08,835
<i>Kosei Neo.</i>

26
00:01:10,403 --> 00:01:14,174
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

27
00:01:17,477 --> 00:01:19,112
<i>Since becoming Eito,</i>

28
00:01:19,779 --> 00:01:21,847
<i>I've now lived through a second spring.</i>

29
00:01:21,848 --> 00:01:23,582
- <i>But…</i>
- <i>Running the government…</i>

30
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:26,385
- <i>…there's still no clue…</i>
- <i>…is difficult.</i>

31
00:01:26,386 --> 00:01:27,587
<i>…no sign of a way back.</i>

32
00:01:31,257 --> 00:01:33,492
<i>The consumer downturn caused</i>

33
00:01:33,493 --> 00:01:36,462
<i>by the sales tax rising to 8%</i>

34
00:01:36,463 --> 00:01:38,898
<i>is severe, and the impact
on the economy is a concern.</i>

35
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:43,502
Compared to the upcoming 10%,
this is nothing.

36
00:01:43,503 --> 00:01:44,837
Huh? Really?

37
00:01:44,838 --> 00:01:45,672
No…

38
00:01:46,506 --> 00:01:48,340
Well, according to my predictions.

39
00:01:48,341 --> 00:01:52,144
Never mind that.
How are things going at NEOXIS?

40
00:01:52,145 --> 00:01:54,580
Being the president's secretary
while preparing for NEOXIS TV

41
00:01:54,581 --> 00:01:56,382
is incredibly demanding.

42
00:01:57,016 --> 00:01:59,218
Is the president managing all right?

43
00:01:59,219 --> 00:02:02,087
Of course.
He's strict when it comes to work,

44
00:02:02,088 --> 00:02:03,323
but everyone respects him.

45
00:02:04,591 --> 00:02:06,792
Is he that great?

46
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:08,293
He really is remarkable.

47
00:02:08,294 --> 00:02:10,762
He has brilliant ideas
and the drive to execute them.

48
00:02:10,763 --> 00:02:13,466
Togo and Tomono have been praising him.

49
00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:15,034
But he really does look

50
00:02:15,735 --> 00:02:17,970
just like you,

51
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:20,206
Brother.

52
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:23,910
Yeah… It's a common face.

53
00:02:24,477 --> 00:02:27,079
But being that talented…

54
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:28,748
Doesn't that invite jealousy?

55
00:02:29,516 --> 00:02:31,084
I don't think so.

56
00:02:32,418 --> 00:02:34,386
Looks good today.

57
00:02:34,387 --> 00:02:35,488
Yeah?

58
00:02:36,122 --> 00:02:38,190
<i>"Looks good," huh?</i>

59
00:02:38,191 --> 00:02:40,093
You really love your bettarazuke.

60
00:02:43,796 --> 00:02:44,697
<i>Well…</i>

61
00:02:45,365 --> 00:02:46,999
<i>I'll leave it at that.</i>

62
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,066
Dinner?

63
00:02:48,067 --> 00:02:48,967
Okay…

64
00:02:48,968 --> 00:02:52,070
<i>The shopping street is thriving,
thanks to me…</i>

65
00:02:52,071 --> 00:02:53,305
Thanks.

66
00:02:53,306 --> 00:02:56,175
- <i>…and yet everyone's still running a tab.</i>
- Thank you.

67
00:02:56,176 --> 00:02:58,777
- <i>Not a single yen coming in.</i>
- Thank you.

68
00:02:58,778 --> 00:03:00,812
Eito!

69
00:03:00,813 --> 00:03:03,782
- Eito!
- Thank you.

70
00:03:03,783 --> 00:03:06,084
- See you!
- When do you want to go?

71
00:03:06,085 --> 00:03:08,120
Eito!

72
00:03:08,121 --> 00:03:09,354
All right!

73
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:11,424
Please.

74
00:03:12,659 --> 00:03:13,860
I'm okay.

75
00:03:18,798 --> 00:03:19,766
Shouldn't you start

76
00:03:20,567 --> 00:03:22,969
making them pay their tabs?

77
00:03:23,736 --> 00:03:27,673
Don't say that.
Everyone's struggling with debt.

78
00:03:27,674 --> 00:03:30,843
But if no money comes in,
even we'll be in trouble.

79
00:03:32,679 --> 00:03:35,180
As the shopping street chairman,

80
00:03:35,181 --> 00:03:37,517
I can't burden everyone.

81
00:03:38,151 --> 00:03:40,519
A man running a 10-million-yen deficit

82
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:42,989
doesn't need to be that noble.

83
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:45,290
Did you say something?

84
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:46,492
No, nothing.

85
00:03:52,632 --> 00:03:54,133
Hello, Nomoto Dry Cleaners.

86
00:03:56,536 --> 00:03:57,837
Is this Kamoshita?

87
00:03:58,838 --> 00:04:00,038
No!

88
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:03,142
Of course I'd love nothing more
than to repay you,

89
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:05,310
but unfortunately,

90
00:04:05,311 --> 00:04:07,580
I simply don't have the means right now.

91
00:04:08,281 --> 00:04:09,648
<i>Are you mocking me?</i>

92
00:04:09,649 --> 00:04:12,618
<i>You used your shop as collateral
when you borrowed money, right?</i>

93
00:04:12,619 --> 00:04:15,955
<i>If you don't repay the 10 million yen
by the end of the month, I'll seize it.</i>

94
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:26,898
Sorry.

95
00:04:26,899 --> 00:04:29,735
I could hear the other side
because they were so loud.

96
00:04:29,736 --> 00:04:31,938
Are they going to take this place?

97
00:04:33,006 --> 00:04:35,741
It's all right. I'll handle it.

98
00:04:35,742 --> 00:04:36,876
Don't worry.

99
00:04:38,378 --> 00:04:40,112
<i>You can't handle anything,</i>

100
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:41,914
<i>so why do you put up a front?</i>

101
00:04:43,316 --> 00:04:44,883
Did you just say something?

102
00:04:44,884 --> 00:04:46,252
I didn't say anything.

103
00:04:48,087 --> 00:04:51,256
<i>But if I don't do something, we'll lose</i>

104
00:04:51,257 --> 00:04:53,025
<i>not just our livelihood</i>

105
00:04:53,026 --> 00:04:55,727
<i>but also our home.</i>

106
00:04:55,728 --> 00:04:57,664
This is the ten million yen
I promised you.

107
00:04:58,398 --> 00:05:01,467
I have a feeling we'll have
a long partnership ahead of us.

108
00:05:06,706 --> 00:05:08,908
<i>I'm well used to seeing
stacks of cash like this,</i>

109
00:05:09,609 --> 00:05:11,411
<i>but I wonder how Eiji will feel about it.</i>

110
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:15,180
Is this money…

111
00:05:15,181 --> 00:05:16,782
tied to something criminal?

112
00:05:16,783 --> 00:05:19,619
What would I even tell my late wife?

113
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,154
<i>Or maybe…</i>

114
00:05:21,721 --> 00:05:23,555
<i>If Eiji is the type to play it cool…</i>

115
00:05:23,556 --> 00:05:24,456
NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

116
00:05:24,457 --> 00:05:25,824
Stop it!

117
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:27,794
You think I can take your money?

118
00:05:29,195 --> 00:05:30,163
<i>Either way,</i>

119
00:05:30,797 --> 00:05:33,366
<i>I need to figure out
a smart way to hand this over.</i>

120
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:36,135
I'll leave your laundry here.

121
00:05:39,706 --> 00:05:40,840
Huh?

122
00:05:42,909 --> 00:05:43,743
Oh.

123
00:05:44,711 --> 00:05:45,945
Where did you get that money?

124
00:05:47,213 --> 00:05:48,047
Well, uh…

125
00:05:49,982 --> 00:05:51,351
The thing is…

126
00:05:52,719 --> 00:05:55,688
What was it…

127
00:05:56,422 --> 00:05:58,523
Oh, right. It was horse racing.

128
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:01,561
I won this, so…

129
00:06:02,428 --> 00:06:06,098
I'd like you to use this
to pay off the debt.

130
00:06:06,099 --> 00:06:06,999
Here.

131
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:20,879
Eito, you did it!

132
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:23,149
With this, the debt is cleared!

133
00:06:23,816 --> 00:06:29,321
Yeah!

134
00:06:29,322 --> 00:06:31,890
- Yeah!
- That's your reaction?

135
00:06:31,891 --> 00:06:33,925
WELCOME TO AKARI SHOPPING STREET

136
00:06:33,926 --> 00:06:36,228
FRUIT AND VEGETABLE SHOP

137
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:37,229
- Hey!
- Hold on!

138
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,930
<i>Little do they know that</i>

139
00:06:38,931 --> 00:06:41,099
<i>ten years from now, they'll be forced out</i>

140
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,834
- <i>by NEOXIS's pressure campaign…</i>
- Okay…

141
00:06:42,835 --> 00:06:44,069
- Okay.
- All right.

142
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:46,371
- <i>Commoners celebrating…</i>
- Thank you.

143
00:06:46,372 --> 00:06:47,806
Okay. One croquette.

144
00:06:47,807 --> 00:06:48,874
- <i>…for now.</i>
- Okay.

145
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:50,242
All right.

146
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:51,910
- Just a moment.
- Three croquettes…

147
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:54,547
- <i>Even living as Eito…</i>
- Three croquettes…

148
00:06:55,181 --> 00:06:58,984
- <i>…the current me has no purpose.</i>
- Here you go.

149
00:06:58,985 --> 00:07:01,987
- Eito! Let's play mahjong!
- Oh!

150
00:07:01,988 --> 00:07:02,988
Mahjong?

151
00:07:02,989 --> 00:07:05,224
You want to win back your losses, right?

152
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,428
Ron!

153
00:07:09,429 --> 00:07:10,896
Closed hand, all simples, one-shot win!

154
00:07:10,897 --> 00:07:11,830
Concealed quad!

155
00:07:11,831 --> 00:07:13,833
- Huh?
- What?

156
00:07:14,734 --> 00:07:17,536
- Ron!
- All suits straight, red dragon!

157
00:07:17,537 --> 00:07:18,838
- Huh?
- What?

158
00:07:20,239 --> 00:07:21,474
Self-draw! Big Three Dragons,

159
00:07:22,175 --> 00:07:23,575
- maximum hand.
- What?

160
00:07:23,576 --> 00:07:25,444
What's with Eito today?

161
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,913
He's so strong. He's like a changed man!

162
00:07:27,914 --> 00:07:29,649
Are you really Eito?

163
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:31,684
<i>They're too weak.</i>

164
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:34,953
<i>Easy pickings</i>

165
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,422
<i>against fools, but don't overdo it.</i>

166
00:07:39,025 --> 00:07:44,563
<i>Still, what a pointless waste of time.</i>

167
00:07:44,564 --> 00:07:46,132
By the way…

168
00:07:46,866 --> 00:07:48,401
what ever happened with Sarasa?

169
00:07:48,968 --> 00:07:50,302
Huh?

170
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:52,737
You proposed to her, didn't you?

171
00:07:52,738 --> 00:07:54,373
- Proposed?
- Yeah.

172
00:07:55,341 --> 00:07:57,776
Are you going to pretend
it never happened?

173
00:07:57,777 --> 00:07:59,245
Even though you went that far…

174
00:08:01,447 --> 00:08:02,482
<i>Now I finally understand</i>

175
00:08:03,249 --> 00:08:05,550
<i>what that was all about.</i>

176
00:08:05,551 --> 00:08:07,986
You were laughing like,
"Even if she says no,

177
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:09,422
at least I'll have a good story."

178
00:08:10,957 --> 00:08:14,025
<i>I'd turn even that into a joke?</i>

179
00:08:14,026 --> 00:08:15,494
<i>Unbelievable.</i>

180
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:17,963
<i>Kosei Neo would never do that.</i>

181
00:08:17,964 --> 00:08:20,966
<i>Even with the same face,
I'm a completely different person.</i>

182
00:08:20,967 --> 00:08:21,867
Well,

183
00:08:21,868 --> 00:08:24,437
I think Sarasa's happy.

184
00:08:24,937 --> 00:08:27,306
She liked you since she was a kid.

185
00:08:28,708 --> 00:08:30,141
<i>Oh, really?</i>

186
00:08:30,142 --> 00:08:33,245
She'd cry or trip on purpose
to get Eito's attention…

187
00:08:33,246 --> 00:08:35,213
She'd fuss over his little sister Eri

188
00:08:35,214 --> 00:08:38,984
- and look after her.
- Handmade presents for him every birthday.

189
00:08:38,985 --> 00:08:41,119
All that effort paid off, and she got

190
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,854
a proposal from Eito!

191
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:44,222
Yeah!

192
00:08:44,223 --> 00:08:46,292
<i>So that's how it was.</i>

193
00:08:48,961 --> 00:08:50,161
- Hey, Eito!
- Huh?

194
00:08:50,162 --> 00:08:51,263
- It's your turn.
- Eito!

195
00:08:51,264 --> 00:08:52,464
- Hey!
- Eito!

196
00:08:52,465 --> 00:08:53,598
Huh?

197
00:08:53,599 --> 00:08:55,567
- Where is he going?
- Huh?

198
00:08:55,568 --> 00:08:57,435
Wait. Did he have a winning hand?

199
00:08:57,436 --> 00:08:58,336
He won!

200
00:08:58,337 --> 00:08:59,538
- Jackpot!
- Oh!

201
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:00,673
- Wait!
- Eito!

202
00:09:04,443 --> 00:09:07,512
<i>I'm acting as the friendly Eito,</i>

203
00:09:07,513 --> 00:09:08,915
<i>but inside, I’m me.</i>

204
00:09:09,649 --> 00:09:11,150
<i>I'm Kosei Neo.</i>

205
00:09:12,084 --> 00:09:13,419
<i>If I marry Sarasa,</i>

206
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:16,155
<i>she won't be happy.</i>

207
00:09:17,990 --> 00:09:20,792
<i>But since I already proposed,</i>

208
00:09:20,793 --> 00:09:23,029
<i>I can’t just pretend it never happened.</i>

209
00:09:23,829 --> 00:09:26,799
<i>I need a convincing reason
to turn it down.</i>

210
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,434
<i>On top of that,</i>

211
00:09:29,435 --> 00:09:31,970
<i>is there a way</i>

212
00:09:31,971 --> 00:09:33,539
<i>to lead her to happiness?</i>

213
00:09:34,373 --> 00:09:36,308
<i>First, I need to gather information.</i>

214
00:09:36,309 --> 00:09:38,510
- Oh!
- Ow!

215
00:09:38,511 --> 00:09:40,011
- You'll slim down.
- What?

216
00:09:40,012 --> 00:09:43,516
What do you think would make Sarasa happy?

217
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:45,383
Well, getting married

218
00:09:45,384 --> 00:09:48,486
and building a happy home, right?

219
00:09:48,487 --> 00:09:50,322
She'd want at least three kids too.

220
00:09:50,323 --> 00:09:52,090
- Huh?
- Huh?

221
00:09:52,091 --> 00:09:54,693
What are you going to do, Eito?
Are you confident about,

222
00:09:54,694 --> 00:09:56,895
- you know, the nighttime side of things?
- No!

223
00:09:56,896 --> 00:09:58,331
<i>Dirty jokes?</i>

224
00:09:58,898 --> 00:10:02,901
Sarasa is Kinpei's daughter.

225
00:10:02,902 --> 00:10:04,603
I don't think she dislikes you.

226
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:05,670
Yeah!

227
00:10:05,671 --> 00:10:07,706
- <i>These two are useless. I guess…</i>
- Yeah!

228
00:10:07,707 --> 00:10:08,607
Yeah!

229
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:09,742
<i>I'll talk to her directly.</i>

230
00:10:10,309 --> 00:10:15,047
IKETANI PRINTING FACTORY

231
00:10:39,505 --> 00:10:43,008
I gave up on that a long time ago.

232
00:10:43,009 --> 00:10:44,343
AKARI-NU

233
00:11:00,526 --> 00:11:01,761
This is it.

234
00:11:20,312 --> 00:11:23,282
I wanted to apologize for the other day.

235
00:11:26,485 --> 00:11:27,420
I never intended

236
00:11:28,054 --> 00:11:29,989
to pretend it didn't happen.

237
00:11:31,457 --> 00:11:32,291
But right now…

238
00:11:33,793 --> 00:11:34,994
I don't feel confident…

239
00:11:36,095 --> 00:11:39,932
that I can make you happy.

240
00:11:50,476 --> 00:11:52,378
Explain that more clearly.

241
00:11:55,047 --> 00:11:56,449
Even since leaving the hospital…

242
00:11:58,084 --> 00:12:01,352
I still have headaches, dizziness,

243
00:12:01,353 --> 00:12:02,188
and chest pain.

244
00:12:03,456 --> 00:12:04,290
Huh?

245
00:12:04,990 --> 00:12:07,927
I might not have long.

246
00:12:09,929 --> 00:12:10,863
So please…

247
00:12:13,966 --> 00:12:15,835
let me think.

248
00:12:17,636 --> 00:12:19,971
I don't want you to die.

249
00:12:19,972 --> 00:12:21,841
Are you going to the hospital?

250
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:24,310
I am. But right now,

251
00:12:25,644 --> 00:12:27,312
more than my own situation,

252
00:12:27,313 --> 00:12:28,814
it's your art, Sarasa.

253
00:12:35,454 --> 00:12:36,856
Your paintings are…

254
00:12:38,057 --> 00:12:39,391
extraordinary.

255
00:12:41,494 --> 00:12:42,762
Looking at them again,

256
00:12:44,230 --> 00:12:45,397
this piece especially…

257
00:12:46,499 --> 00:12:48,800
I can feel your love

258
00:12:48,801 --> 00:12:50,569
for the people of this shopping street.

259
00:12:52,238 --> 00:12:53,239
Would you consider

260
00:12:54,573 --> 00:12:56,609
holding a solo exhibition?

261
00:12:59,111 --> 00:13:00,879
What are you talking about?

262
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:03,749
Having a solo exhibition
after dropping out of art school?

263
00:13:06,385 --> 00:13:09,455
Thank you, but I'll accept

264
00:13:09,989 --> 00:13:11,656
the sentiment and leave it at that.

265
00:13:11,657 --> 00:13:14,527
I don't want it to just be sentiment.

266
00:13:19,431 --> 00:13:22,168
I want you to keep painting, Sarasa.

267
00:13:24,503 --> 00:13:26,038
Your work gave me strength.

268
00:13:26,939 --> 00:13:29,141
Anyone else who sees it

269
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:32,311
will feel the same.

270
00:13:38,918 --> 00:13:39,985
Togo.

271
00:13:42,388 --> 00:13:45,557
Surely you weren't waiting for me?

272
00:13:45,558 --> 00:13:48,194
I was hoping we might run into each other.

273
00:13:49,695 --> 00:13:51,897
How did you know I'd come here?

274
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:54,934
A hunch.

275
00:13:57,303 --> 00:14:00,272
This is a work by a woman
named Sarasa Iketani.

276
00:14:00,906 --> 00:14:03,709
I thought I'd give it to you.

277
00:14:05,110 --> 00:14:07,011
Sarasa Iketani?

278
00:14:07,012 --> 00:14:10,115
Yes. She's still unknown for now,

279
00:14:10,783 --> 00:14:13,051
but I believe
she's the next artist who will follow

280
00:14:13,052 --> 00:14:14,553
in the footsteps of Yoshitomo Nara.

281
00:14:15,921 --> 00:14:17,890
Why would you give me the work

282
00:14:18,624 --> 00:14:21,360
- of such a promising artist?
- Of course, I don't intend

283
00:14:22,294 --> 00:14:24,763
to give it away for free.

284
00:14:26,131 --> 00:14:29,235
You who value my foresight…

285
00:14:29,935 --> 00:14:31,569
I was hoping

286
00:14:31,570 --> 00:14:34,139
you might lend your strength
to help bring her into the world.

287
00:14:39,178 --> 00:14:40,779
You know, you once told me

288
00:14:42,848 --> 00:14:45,651
this might be the start

289
00:14:46,151 --> 00:14:47,653
of a long relationship.

290
00:14:48,687 --> 00:14:50,222
In many ways,

291
00:14:51,257 --> 00:14:53,092
you remind me of Neo.

292
00:14:55,494 --> 00:14:57,363
You remind me so much of him that I…

293
00:14:59,031 --> 00:15:00,866
I had someone look into you.

294
00:15:11,810 --> 00:15:13,479
No connection at all.

295
00:15:14,613 --> 00:15:16,382
A complete stranger.

296
00:15:21,887 --> 00:15:23,689
Shall we have some champagne?

297
00:15:24,189 --> 00:15:25,024
Yes.

298
00:15:32,131 --> 00:15:33,031
Here.

299
00:15:33,032 --> 00:15:33,932
GINZA CHISEIDO GALLERY

300
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:36,635
Your solo exhibition has been arranged.

301
00:15:37,469 --> 00:15:39,337
At the Ginza Chiseido Gallery?

302
00:15:39,338 --> 00:15:41,407
Are you serious?

303
00:15:42,908 --> 00:15:44,008
In your art school days,

304
00:15:44,009 --> 00:15:46,744
you swept every prize.

305
00:15:46,745 --> 00:15:48,113
This is only natural for you.

306
00:15:48,681 --> 00:15:49,981
No…

307
00:15:49,982 --> 00:15:53,351
But still, out of nowhere,
doing it in a place

308
00:15:53,352 --> 00:15:55,153
like this? There's no way I could.

309
00:15:55,154 --> 00:15:58,057
Right, normally, you couldn't.

310
00:15:58,724 --> 00:16:01,726
A major investor has taken notice

311
00:16:01,727 --> 00:16:03,862
of your work.

312
00:16:05,531 --> 00:16:06,564
As usual,

313
00:16:06,565 --> 00:16:09,101
all you need to do is keep painting,
just as you always have.

314
00:16:10,069 --> 00:16:12,804
Sarasa, what about this paper fan?

315
00:16:12,805 --> 00:16:14,340
- Yeah.
- Oh.

316
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:15,808
What is this?

317
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:18,110
This is wonderful!

318
00:16:20,045 --> 00:16:21,846
Oh, you forgot?

319
00:16:21,847 --> 00:16:23,948
Sarasa made this last summer
for the street festival.

320
00:16:23,949 --> 00:16:25,516
- Oh.
- That's right.

321
00:16:25,517 --> 00:16:28,086
I know, but what are we going
to do with it?

322
00:16:28,087 --> 00:16:30,655
I was thinking of selling it
for 100 yen with the toy bin.

323
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:33,726
Absolutely not!
You can't undersell it like that.

324
00:16:34,226 --> 00:16:38,597
Sarasa needs to recognize
the value of her own work.

325
00:16:39,798 --> 00:16:41,600
It is a lovely piece, but getting

326
00:16:42,568 --> 00:16:45,436
NEOXIS TV's arts program

327
00:16:45,437 --> 00:16:47,739
to feature it is
beyond me as a new employee.

328
00:16:47,740 --> 00:16:50,008
But Tomono is the one in charge, right?

329
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:51,943
Huh? How do you know that?

330
00:16:51,944 --> 00:16:54,847
Well, that's because, uh…

331
00:16:55,381 --> 00:16:56,481
Yeah…

332
00:16:56,482 --> 00:16:59,118
Because I've been looking
into things for Sarasa's sake.

333
00:16:59,952 --> 00:17:02,488
Is this painting Sarasa's?

334
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:07,592
Togo, who is a great supporter
of President Neo, is backing her.

335
00:17:07,593 --> 00:17:09,661
President Neo will surely love
the painting too.

336
00:17:11,263 --> 00:17:12,731
How do you know that?

337
00:17:13,966 --> 00:17:15,433
<i>Because I, as Kosei Neo,</i>

338
00:17:15,434 --> 00:17:18,170
<i>loved it myself.</i>

339
00:17:19,304 --> 00:17:20,839
<i>But I can't say that.</i>

340
00:17:22,741 --> 00:17:26,345
<i>Oh, did I upset her again?</i>

341
00:17:31,850 --> 00:17:32,684
All right. Let's go.

342
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:37,890
For Sarasa's sake, I'll do my best.

343
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:43,495
You scared me.

344
00:17:46,231 --> 00:17:48,133
EXHIBITION
SARASA IKETANI

345
00:17:54,606 --> 00:17:56,340
AKARI-NU
MUROTA BUTCHER SHOP

346
00:17:56,341 --> 00:17:58,443
- Congratulations.
- Hello.

347
00:17:58,444 --> 00:17:59,811
Just like my brother said,

348
00:17:59,812 --> 00:18:01,479
even President Neo loved it,

349
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:03,949
and NEOXIS TV is going to feature it.

350
00:18:04,483 --> 00:18:07,418
Her first exhibition
is already this lively,

351
00:18:07,419 --> 00:18:09,187
- and even that famous figure is here.
- Oh!

352
00:18:09,188 --> 00:18:11,889
You're right!
He's a really famous film director.

353
00:18:11,890 --> 00:18:14,626
Togo's influence really is amazing.

354
00:18:15,494 --> 00:18:17,695
But your brother who moved Togo

355
00:18:17,696 --> 00:18:20,231
is also pretty remarkable.

356
00:18:20,232 --> 00:18:22,434
Okay. Who's next?

357
00:18:24,036 --> 00:18:25,838
Sarasa-san, you're amazing!

358
00:18:26,638 --> 00:18:29,006
I'm glad I could help.

359
00:18:29,007 --> 00:18:30,242
Thanks, Eri!

360
00:18:33,846 --> 00:18:37,281
Are you Namioka, the editor-in-chief
of Cosmo culture magazine?

361
00:18:37,282 --> 00:18:39,517
Yes. Can I help you?

362
00:18:39,518 --> 00:18:43,187
This is sudden,
but I'd like you to run a feature

363
00:18:43,188 --> 00:18:46,458
on Sarasa Iketani in this month's issue.

364
00:18:47,226 --> 00:18:49,027
She's still a nobody.

365
00:18:49,895 --> 00:18:52,396
And I have no reason to take requests

366
00:18:52,397 --> 00:18:54,398
from someone I've never met.

367
00:18:54,399 --> 00:18:56,468
But you wouldn't want word to get out

368
00:18:57,002 --> 00:18:59,471
about your affair

369
00:19:00,038 --> 00:19:02,074
with an actress, right?

370
00:19:02,574 --> 00:19:03,541
What do you mean?

371
00:19:03,542 --> 00:19:06,044
The bold actress Kurumi Momota.

372
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:13,418
Huh? What basis do you have
for saying that?

373
00:19:14,319 --> 00:19:15,154
<i>That…</i>

374
00:19:15,721 --> 00:19:17,889
<i>within a year, every tabloid</i>

375
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:20,391
<i>and variety show in Japan will know.</i>

376
00:19:20,392 --> 00:19:21,226
FAMOUS EDITOR "N" HAS AFFAIR
WITH KURUMI MOMOTA

377
00:19:21,793 --> 00:19:25,564
How about it? Will you do it?

378
00:19:27,366 --> 00:19:29,168
I can see you're very passionate.

379
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,369
I'll give it serious thought.

380
00:19:31,370 --> 00:19:32,938
Thank you.

381
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:36,140
Could I get your business card?

382
00:19:36,141 --> 00:19:37,075
Sure.

383
00:19:48,687 --> 00:19:50,389
<i>Sarasa Iketani coming through.</i>

384
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:54,926
- Thank you.
- Thank you!

385
00:19:54,927 --> 00:19:55,961
Thank you.

386
00:19:57,362 --> 00:19:59,163
Thank you.

387
00:19:59,164 --> 00:20:00,966
Beautiful. Lovely.

388
00:20:01,633 --> 00:20:03,936
Yes. A little more of a smile.

389
00:20:04,503 --> 00:20:05,903
Thank you.

390
00:20:05,904 --> 00:20:08,372
Your eyes are so striking.

391
00:20:08,373 --> 00:20:12,043
- I'm going for a slightly sharper look.
- Got it.

392
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:14,046
<i>As expected of Editor Namioka…</i>

393
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,247
<i>He may be a mess in his personal life,</i>

394
00:20:16,248 --> 00:20:18,016
<i>but he's a pro at his job.</i>

395
00:20:20,185 --> 00:20:22,753
A VISIONARY ARTIST
SARASA IKETANI

396
00:20:22,754 --> 00:20:26,591
Hey, Sarasa looks amazing!

397
00:20:26,592 --> 00:20:30,394
- Being on the cover feels like a dream.
- Right?

398
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:33,264
Hey! Our very own shopping street hero!

399
00:20:33,265 --> 00:20:34,498
Yeah!

400
00:20:34,499 --> 00:20:37,702
- Yeah!
- But I feel a bit uncomfortable…

401
00:20:37,703 --> 00:20:41,606
I’d rather let my work speak for itself

402
00:20:41,607 --> 00:20:43,609
- than be out front.
- Wow!

403
00:20:44,142 --> 00:20:47,078
The person in this photo
isn't the real me.

404
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:49,681
It's a version of me
from a fictional world.

405
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:53,651
So what is the real you?

406
00:20:53,652 --> 00:20:55,220
Can you explain?

407
00:20:57,289 --> 00:21:00,825
No one goes through life
truly knowing who they really are.

408
00:21:00,826 --> 00:21:01,827
And sometimes,

409
00:21:02,894 --> 00:21:05,097
you have to play
a version of yourself that isn't real.

410
00:21:06,965 --> 00:21:08,500
What's wrong with fiction?

411
00:21:09,034 --> 00:21:12,570
Art is art precisely because truth
and fiction coexist.

412
00:21:12,571 --> 00:21:14,605
That's why your paintings are so powerful.

413
00:21:14,606 --> 00:21:17,508
- Getting philosophical, are we?
- Right?

414
00:21:17,509 --> 00:21:19,177
It's entertainment.

415
00:21:19,745 --> 00:21:21,245
You just have to embrace both

416
00:21:21,246 --> 00:21:23,181
truth and fiction and enjoy the ride.

417
00:21:24,616 --> 00:21:26,318
Going out into the world means

418
00:21:26,952 --> 00:21:28,586
being discovered by others,

419
00:21:28,587 --> 00:21:31,490
becoming theirs, being consumed.

420
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:35,060
Misunderstood, evaluated, all of it.

421
00:21:35,761 --> 00:21:37,562
You have to be ready for all of that.

422
00:21:43,769 --> 00:21:45,037
No…

423
00:21:47,272 --> 00:21:50,909
I was the one who pushed this forward.

424
00:21:51,643 --> 00:21:54,779
If it was a burden to you, we can stop.

425
00:21:54,780 --> 00:21:56,847
- Not at all.
- No.

426
00:21:56,848 --> 00:21:59,017
That's not what I meant.

427
00:22:00,686 --> 00:22:03,788
Like… I'm sorry
for saying something strange.

428
00:22:03,789 --> 00:22:04,723
No…

429
00:22:05,957 --> 00:22:08,327
Same here.

430
00:22:10,128 --> 00:22:10,962
Huh?

431
00:22:11,463 --> 00:22:12,463
How about a toast?

432
00:22:12,464 --> 00:22:14,265
- Right!
- Oh, yeah!

433
00:22:14,266 --> 00:22:16,701
- Toast!
- Right!

434
00:22:16,702 --> 00:22:21,940
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

435
00:22:23,175 --> 00:22:24,241
But…

436
00:22:24,242 --> 00:22:26,477
- Come on!
- <i>What was I thinking?</i>

437
00:22:26,478 --> 00:22:27,645
Right?

438
00:22:27,646 --> 00:22:30,549
<i>Finally, I let my true feelings slip out.</i>

439
00:22:33,452 --> 00:22:35,086
- <i>Still…</i>
- I'll be late.

440
00:22:35,087 --> 00:22:38,055
<i>…this household's table
keeps getting poorer.</i>

441
00:22:38,056 --> 00:22:39,757
NEOXIS TV…

442
00:22:39,758 --> 00:22:43,027
<i>At this rate, Burgundy wine</i>

443
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:44,495
<i>is just a dream.</i>

444
00:22:44,496 --> 00:22:47,232
It takes a lot of effort to prepare.

445
00:22:47,766 --> 00:22:50,801
<i>Nations around the world are alarmed</i>

446
00:22:50,802 --> 00:22:53,204
<i>as global warming is expected to be raised</i>

447
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:56,608
<i>as a top priority
at this autumn's UN General Assembly.</i>

448
00:22:57,476 --> 00:22:59,443
- Dad, you…
- Yeah.

449
00:22:59,444 --> 00:23:00,945
- That's it.
- Huh?

450
00:23:00,946 --> 00:23:04,548
- Huh?
- <i>…efforts to cut CO2 emissions…</i>

451
00:23:04,549 --> 00:23:07,918
Turning climate change into a business?

452
00:23:07,919 --> 00:23:11,722
Exactly. Let's all launch
a climate business together.

453
00:23:11,723 --> 00:23:13,758
Will that actually make money?

454
00:23:13,759 --> 00:23:16,060
Of course. The SDGs will be adopted

455
00:23:16,061 --> 00:23:17,695
at the autumn UN Assembly,

456
00:23:17,696 --> 00:23:20,364
and climate businesses
will be in the spotlight.

457
00:23:20,365 --> 00:23:24,001
Climate goods should finally
get their day in the sun.

458
00:23:24,002 --> 00:23:26,504
There he goes again
with the complicated stuff.

459
00:23:26,505 --> 00:23:27,405
- Right?
- Yeah.

460
00:23:27,406 --> 00:23:31,041
Ever since he hit his head,
he's been a bit odd.

461
00:23:31,042 --> 00:23:33,411
So let's all start a company

462
00:23:33,412 --> 00:23:35,680
to earn money together.

463
00:23:36,248 --> 00:23:38,884
The name will be
Akari Shopping Street Co., Ltd.

464
00:23:39,451 --> 00:23:41,419
Akari Shopping Street Co., Ltd.?

465
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:42,887
- That's literally the name!
- Really…

466
00:23:42,888 --> 00:23:44,955
- What kind of name is that?
- Right!

467
00:23:44,956 --> 00:23:46,657
But you know…

468
00:23:46,658 --> 00:23:50,394
But if Eito says it'll make money,
why not give it a shot?

469
00:23:50,395 --> 00:23:52,363
If we're starting a company,
who will the president be?

470
00:23:52,364 --> 00:23:53,964
- Right.
- Yeah.

471
00:23:53,965 --> 00:23:55,466
I'd like…

472
00:23:55,467 --> 00:23:58,670
to ask the shopping street chairman,
my dad, to take the role.

473
00:23:59,171 --> 00:24:00,504
- Really?
- Huh?

474
00:24:00,505 --> 00:24:02,940
Me? President?

475
00:24:02,941 --> 00:24:06,644
There'll be a lot of hard work,
but I'll be there to support you.

476
00:24:06,645 --> 00:24:08,179
- Wow!
- No.

477
00:24:08,180 --> 00:24:10,481
- He looks happy!
- Yeah!

478
00:24:10,482 --> 00:24:12,316
- President?
- Sounds good!

479
00:24:12,317 --> 00:24:15,386
- Yeah!
- Come on!

480
00:24:15,387 --> 00:24:17,221
If Eito says so, I can't refuse!

481
00:24:17,222 --> 00:24:20,558
- Wow!
- Yeah!

482
00:24:20,559 --> 00:24:23,027
- Hurray!
- Yeah!

483
00:24:23,028 --> 00:24:25,095
<i>And with this, our household</i>

484
00:24:25,096 --> 00:24:27,531
<i>will finally see some income.</i>

485
00:24:27,532 --> 00:24:28,867
Yeah!

486
00:24:31,069 --> 00:24:32,671
What do you think? How does this look?

487
00:24:39,010 --> 00:24:40,378
Nice!

488
00:24:44,716 --> 00:24:46,084
Nice!

489
00:24:49,955 --> 00:24:51,755
- You're late.
- Oh.

490
00:24:51,756 --> 00:24:53,757
Sorry for the wait, President!

491
00:24:53,758 --> 00:24:54,726
- Huh?
- What?

492
00:24:59,297 --> 00:25:01,433
- Nice!
- Really?

493
00:25:01,933 --> 00:25:03,167
This is nice!

494
00:25:03,168 --> 00:25:06,004
GLOBAL WARMING COUNTERMEASURES FAIR

495
00:25:08,507 --> 00:25:10,007
- There's a spray!
- Nice.

496
00:25:10,008 --> 00:25:12,877
- Isn't it good?
- Maybe pink for me?

497
00:25:12,878 --> 00:25:13,611
How is it?

498
00:25:13,612 --> 00:25:15,246
This is super cool.

499
00:25:15,247 --> 00:25:16,447
- Wow!
- Amazing!

500
00:25:16,448 --> 00:25:18,382
- Right?
- Thank you.

501
00:25:18,383 --> 00:25:20,485
- It's Akari-nu!
- So cute!

502
00:25:21,152 --> 00:25:22,186
Nice, isn't it?

503
00:25:22,187 --> 00:25:23,087
AKARI-NU

504
00:25:23,088 --> 00:25:24,523
By the way,

505
00:25:25,257 --> 00:25:28,994
you've been wearing suits lately.
Looks expensive.

506
00:25:29,694 --> 00:25:30,929
I'm the president now.

507
00:25:31,429 --> 00:25:33,131
I need to look the part.

508
00:25:35,267 --> 00:25:38,636
Found him!
Eiji, someone was looking for you.

509
00:25:38,637 --> 00:25:42,439
Inose, from now on,
could you call me "President"?

510
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:43,308
Huh?

511
00:25:49,881 --> 00:25:51,116
President!

512
00:25:51,917 --> 00:25:52,817
<i>Apparently,</i>

513
00:25:53,385 --> 00:25:55,586
<i>he's really taken a liking</i>

514
00:25:55,587 --> 00:25:57,322
- <i>to the title of president.</i>
- Doing his best…

515
00:25:59,157 --> 00:26:01,159
Are you mocking me?

516
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:05,129
You promised to repay this quickly.

517
00:26:05,130 --> 00:26:07,798
Just a moment, please.

518
00:26:07,799 --> 00:26:10,634
Wasn't Dad supposed to have
already paid off the debt?

519
00:26:10,635 --> 00:26:11,570
Huh?

520
00:26:14,706 --> 00:26:16,474
He borrowed again.

521
00:26:19,844 --> 00:26:21,379
I'm sorry, Kamoshita.

522
00:26:22,347 --> 00:26:23,915
I'll repay you soon.

523
00:26:25,650 --> 00:26:27,985
If that turns out to be a lie,

524
00:26:27,986 --> 00:26:30,589
I'll seize this house for real.

525
00:26:33,892 --> 00:26:40,364
‎NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

526
00:26:40,365 --> 00:26:41,299
Dad…

527
00:26:42,634 --> 00:26:45,637
What is this all about?

528
00:26:47,372 --> 00:26:48,772
Yeah…

529
00:26:48,773 --> 00:26:50,408
Life throws all kinds of things at you.

530
00:26:52,577 --> 00:26:53,645
You borrowed again?

531
00:26:55,981 --> 00:26:57,349
I'm sorry, Eito.

532
00:26:59,150 --> 00:27:00,151
The truth is…

533
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:12,597
<i>I found a suit befitting
a company president, and well…</i>

534
00:27:13,965 --> 00:27:14,966
How much?

535
00:27:16,401 --> 00:27:18,370
Three hundred…

536
00:27:19,537 --> 00:27:20,705
thousand yen.

537
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:29,813
This too?

538
00:27:29,814 --> 00:27:31,549
A president also needs

539
00:27:32,217 --> 00:27:35,020
a proper watch, right?

540
00:27:35,620 --> 00:27:37,455
- How much?
- One million yen.

541
00:27:42,360 --> 00:27:43,461
Anything else?

542
00:27:44,362 --> 00:27:47,931
I also went to a Ginza club…

543
00:27:47,932 --> 00:27:50,135
A Ginza club?

544
00:27:51,836 --> 00:27:53,504
Well, you know…

545
00:27:53,505 --> 00:27:56,274
A president needs to be
comfortable in places like that.

546
00:27:56,941 --> 00:27:58,476
<i>Where is all this coming from?</i>

547
00:27:59,077 --> 00:28:01,845
<i>This warped idea of a president?</i>

548
00:28:01,846 --> 00:28:03,314
And then a hostess who looked like Mom

549
00:28:04,282 --> 00:28:06,718
in her younger days

550
00:28:07,352 --> 00:28:09,654
asked me out outside of work.

551
00:28:10,588 --> 00:28:11,890
She asked me for a designer bag…

552
00:28:13,725 --> 00:28:14,758
You bought it?

553
00:28:14,759 --> 00:28:16,394
That's what presidents do, right?

554
00:28:17,562 --> 00:28:18,830
How much?

555
00:28:20,398 --> 00:28:21,232
800,000 yen.

556
00:28:27,038 --> 00:28:28,006
So in total…

557
00:28:29,641 --> 00:28:31,376
how much did you borrow?

558
00:28:32,243 --> 00:28:33,911
I thought I'd win it back

559
00:28:33,912 --> 00:28:35,814
at the horse races, so including that…

560
00:28:38,083 --> 00:28:38,917
4 million yen.

561
00:28:40,485 --> 00:28:43,354
<i>A truly hopeless owner.</i>

562
00:28:46,958 --> 00:28:47,926
What should I do?

563
00:28:49,794 --> 00:28:50,829
You can't figure that out…

564
00:28:52,130 --> 00:28:53,765
on your own?

565
00:28:56,468 --> 00:28:58,669
If you don't want to lose this house,

566
00:28:58,670 --> 00:29:02,406
what you need to do is generate profit

567
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:04,409
as the president
of Akari Shopping Street Co., Ltd.!

568
00:29:10,281 --> 00:29:11,483
Are you angry?

569
00:29:11,983 --> 00:29:14,252
Of course I'm angry!

570
00:29:17,088 --> 00:29:17,989
<i>This is hopeless.</i>

571
00:29:18,590 --> 00:29:21,692
<i>Even with a goal, it's hopeless.</i>

572
00:29:21,693 --> 00:29:24,429
<i>Being here is hopeless.
Back to the original world…</i>

573
00:29:29,834 --> 00:29:32,237
<i>It never occurred to me before.</i>

574
00:29:33,271 --> 00:29:35,740
<i>If I collide with him
the same way I did then,</i>

575
00:29:36,608 --> 00:29:38,910
<i>maybe I can get back to my original world.</i>

576
00:29:39,978 --> 00:29:43,381
<i>In movies and novels,
that's the classic solution.</i>

577
00:29:44,649 --> 00:29:46,151
Don't move no matter what happens.

578
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:47,685
What are you doing?

579
00:29:49,554 --> 00:29:50,522
I'm going to fall.

580
00:29:51,656 --> 00:29:52,590
That's dangerous.

581
00:30:01,833 --> 00:30:02,933
Dammit!

582
00:30:02,934 --> 00:30:04,602
<i>Why are you hesitating?</i>

583
00:30:06,738 --> 00:30:09,641
<i>Right…
Looking down is what makes it scary.</i>

584
00:30:15,246 --> 00:30:17,182
No! Dammit!

585
00:30:18,583 --> 00:30:21,653
Good enough, Eito?
I've got somewhere to be.

586
00:30:23,688 --> 00:30:24,589
Sure.

587
00:30:27,192 --> 00:30:28,493
Go ahead. Sorry.

588
00:30:29,194 --> 00:30:32,397
ONE WEEK LATER

589
00:30:33,531 --> 00:30:36,067
This is a request from me as president.

590
00:30:38,136 --> 00:30:40,605
I'd like these climate goods

591
00:30:41,339 --> 00:30:43,942
to be sold
through your company's online store.

592
00:30:45,443 --> 00:30:48,846
Look, even if you ask,

593
00:30:48,847 --> 00:30:50,948
there's really not much I can do.

594
00:30:50,949 --> 00:30:52,483
But…

595
00:30:53,151 --> 00:30:55,853
the big online retailers are squeezing us

596
00:30:55,854 --> 00:30:57,188
with unfavorable terms.

597
00:30:58,556 --> 00:31:01,392
I've talked to several companies,
but they weren't worth talking to.

598
00:31:03,494 --> 00:31:05,129
<i>This is surprising.</i>

599
00:31:05,964 --> 00:31:08,166
<i>This hopeless owner</i>

600
00:31:08,733 --> 00:31:10,735
<i>has been trying his best, in his own way.</i>

601
00:31:11,302 --> 00:31:15,206
A backstreet shopping district like this
gets looked down on and ignored.

602
00:31:17,542 --> 00:31:18,943
Please, Eri.

603
00:31:23,748 --> 00:31:25,283
I know you're in a tough spot.

604
00:31:26,417 --> 00:31:29,153
I'll at least ask around.

605
00:31:30,555 --> 00:31:33,358
<i>Actually, this could be interesting…</i>

606
00:31:34,158 --> 00:31:36,994
<i>Products developed by Kosei Neo,</i>

607
00:31:36,995 --> 00:31:39,264
<i>sold by Kosei Neo's company.</i>

608
00:31:42,500 --> 00:31:43,635
GLOBAL WARMING COUNTERMEASURES PRODUCTS
2015

609
00:31:46,504 --> 00:31:48,072
I'm against it.

610
00:31:49,173 --> 00:31:51,375
Supporting a family business

611
00:31:51,376 --> 00:31:53,243
would look like favoritism,

612
00:31:53,244 --> 00:31:56,080
and with President Neo's personality,
he might even fire you.

613
00:31:58,283 --> 00:31:59,783
But Tomono,

614
00:31:59,784 --> 00:32:03,321
couldn't you at least look
at the contents first before deciding?

615
00:32:04,055 --> 00:32:04,956
All right.

616
00:32:21,973 --> 00:32:23,775
These are exceptional.

617
00:32:25,276 --> 00:32:27,911
Your brother might actually be a genius.

618
00:32:27,912 --> 00:32:30,914
NEOXIS TV shopping!

619
00:32:30,915 --> 00:32:33,216
Today, we're introducing products
to help you

620
00:32:33,217 --> 00:32:36,720
through the scorching heat
caused by global warming.

621
00:32:36,721 --> 00:32:40,090
All of these were developed
by a local shopping street,

622
00:32:40,091 --> 00:32:43,760
infused with the warmth of the community.

623
00:32:43,761 --> 00:32:46,763
We'll be announcing an unbelievable price.

624
00:32:46,764 --> 00:32:48,665
Everyone, history is about to be made!

625
00:32:48,666 --> 00:32:51,501
That jaw-dropping price
is coming up very soon.

626
00:32:51,502 --> 00:32:52,070
THE JAW-DROPPING PRICE?

627
00:32:55,807 --> 00:32:57,976
Turning climate change into a business…

628
00:32:58,910 --> 00:33:01,112
Your foresight is genuine.

629
00:33:01,679 --> 00:33:04,582
I just happened to think of it.

630
00:33:08,553 --> 00:33:11,289
In return for promoting
Sarasa's exhibition,

631
00:33:12,690 --> 00:33:14,192
I want to ask you something.

632
00:33:16,494 --> 00:33:19,063
If you had
my financial resources right now,

633
00:33:20,465 --> 00:33:21,432
what would you do?

634
00:33:23,801 --> 00:33:25,837
<i>ECONOMIC STRUCTURE</i>

635
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:31,942
This, I believe.

636
00:33:31,943 --> 00:33:33,911
CAN JAPANESE SEMICONDUCTORS
MAKE A COMEBACK?

637
00:33:35,313 --> 00:33:37,181
Semiconductors, which are currently

638
00:33:37,815 --> 00:33:39,116
a dying industry here in Japan…

639
00:33:39,117 --> 00:33:41,451
I think the day will come again

640
00:33:41,452 --> 00:33:44,555
when the whole country
pours its energy into semiconductors.

641
00:33:47,291 --> 00:33:49,260
I'll take that under advisement,

642
00:33:50,461 --> 00:33:53,631
savior of the back streets.

643
00:33:55,633 --> 00:33:57,869
<i>"Savior of the back streets"?</i>

644
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:00,370
- Eito!
- Oh!

645
00:34:00,371 --> 00:34:01,339
Eito!

646
00:34:04,509 --> 00:34:05,777
<i>Come to think of it…</i>

647
00:34:06,644 --> 00:34:09,714
<i>Whether to survive
or to meet some goals of mine,</i>

648
00:34:10,515 --> 00:34:12,550
<i>since becoming Eito, I've been saving</i>

649
00:34:13,117 --> 00:34:16,020
<i>the Akari Shopping Street all along.</i>

650
00:34:16,654 --> 00:34:17,854
GLOBAL WARMING COUNTERMEASURES FAIR

651
00:34:17,855 --> 00:34:19,689
<i>As Kosei Neo…</i>

652
00:34:19,690 --> 00:34:21,691
- It's hot.
- <i>…it was an area I was going to destroy.</i>

653
00:34:21,692 --> 00:34:23,727
- Let's switch.
- Thank you!

654
00:34:23,728 --> 00:34:24,628
Thank you.

655
00:34:24,629 --> 00:34:26,730
- Okay. Thank you!
- Thank you!

656
00:34:26,731 --> 00:34:28,999
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

657
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:30,734
Thank you!

658
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:33,103
President! It went well!

659
00:34:33,104 --> 00:34:35,972
Mr. Great President!

660
00:34:35,973 --> 00:34:39,509
- A great president!
- You even got the TV channel involved!

661
00:34:39,510 --> 00:34:41,446
- Right.
- Here's a gift.

662
00:34:42,380 --> 00:34:44,648
- Thank you!
- No way!

663
00:34:44,649 --> 00:34:48,385
To think Eiji could pull off
this much as a president.

664
00:34:48,386 --> 00:34:50,854
- No, it's all…
- Wait!

665
00:34:50,855 --> 00:34:53,524
-…thanks to Eito.
- Thanks to Eito?

666
00:34:54,759 --> 00:34:56,593
Because of Eito,
I was finally able to face

667
00:34:56,594 --> 00:34:59,063
how useless I'd been.

668
00:34:59,964 --> 00:35:02,800
I finally decided to work hard.

669
00:35:04,102 --> 00:35:05,669
What are you saying?

670
00:35:05,670 --> 00:35:07,270
You went through a lot,

671
00:35:07,271 --> 00:35:08,706
but you worked hard too, Dad.

672
00:35:09,373 --> 00:35:10,208
Still…

673
00:35:11,175 --> 00:35:12,210
it's because you were there.

674
00:35:15,213 --> 00:35:16,247
I'm grateful too.

675
00:35:21,986 --> 00:35:24,455
I'm beyond grateful too.

676
00:35:25,356 --> 00:35:28,659
Thanks to Eito, Sarasa's life was saved,

677
00:35:29,227 --> 00:35:32,330
- and she has a solo exhibition.
- Same for me.

678
00:35:32,930 --> 00:35:36,534
Thanks to Eito,
I sold a ton of croquettes.

679
00:35:37,235 --> 00:35:39,536
After that accident,

680
00:35:39,537 --> 00:35:41,938
I'm just so grateful you didn't die, Eito.

681
00:35:41,939 --> 00:35:43,507
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

682
00:35:43,508 --> 00:35:45,942
Hey! You know, Eito…

683
00:35:45,943 --> 00:35:47,878
You're truly

684
00:35:47,879 --> 00:35:49,514
the savior of Akari Shopping Street!

685
00:35:52,216 --> 00:35:53,050
No…

686
00:35:55,219 --> 00:35:56,686
I'm not that.

687
00:35:56,687 --> 00:35:58,788
<i>The Akari Housing Complex</i>

688
00:35:58,789 --> 00:36:00,323
and Akari Shopping Street…

689
00:36:00,324 --> 00:36:02,792
Feel free to spend the money.
We want to move quickly.

690
00:36:02,793 --> 00:36:05,897
We won't sell our hometown for money.

691
00:36:07,965 --> 00:36:09,666
<i>Double the payout.</i>

692
00:36:09,667 --> 00:36:11,034
<i>I hope you can see</i>

693
00:36:11,035 --> 00:36:12,502
what a favorable deal this is.

694
00:36:12,503 --> 00:36:14,871
- I'm not falling for that kind of talk!
- Me too!

695
00:36:14,872 --> 00:36:16,306
<i>I'm going to give these people</i>

696
00:36:16,307 --> 00:36:18,542
<i>the money they'll need going forward.</i>

697
00:36:18,543 --> 00:36:19,343
Push for five times.

698
00:36:35,893 --> 00:36:38,628
Stop being embarrassed, Eito!

699
00:36:38,629 --> 00:36:41,598
You've always been the best of all of us!

700
00:36:41,599 --> 00:36:43,167
Hey, everyone, listen up!

701
00:36:43,801 --> 00:36:45,335
Tonight, in Eito's honor,

702
00:36:45,336 --> 00:36:48,004
I'm treating everyone to the best drinks!

703
00:36:48,005 --> 00:36:50,073
- Oh!
- Yeah!

704
00:36:50,074 --> 00:36:51,641
Go get some!

705
00:36:51,642 --> 00:36:52,710
- Okay.
- Yeah…

706
00:36:54,679 --> 00:36:56,013
What's wrong with him?

707
00:37:01,552 --> 00:37:03,955
- Eito!
- Eito!

708
00:37:14,932 --> 00:37:16,266
Around here…

709
00:37:16,267 --> 00:37:18,169
- Later!
- See you!

710
00:37:25,643 --> 00:37:26,544
Eito!

711
00:37:27,144 --> 00:37:28,546
Come over here!

712
00:37:40,658 --> 00:37:41,993
It's beautiful.

713
00:37:44,362 --> 00:37:46,397
It's my hometown, after all.

714
00:37:48,833 --> 00:37:50,568
Looking at this river,

715
00:37:51,235 --> 00:37:52,937
so many things come back to me.

716
00:37:54,538 --> 00:37:57,874
Like when I fell into the river as a kid

717
00:37:57,875 --> 00:38:00,177
and you saved me.

718
00:38:01,012 --> 00:38:03,813
When I was crying
after dropping out of art school,

719
00:38:03,814 --> 00:38:06,884
you stayed by my side the whole time.

720
00:38:10,855 --> 00:38:12,957
Eito was such a good person.

721
00:38:13,691 --> 00:38:15,960
He still is… Always…

722
00:38:16,727 --> 00:38:17,695
Even now.

723
00:38:23,701 --> 00:38:25,835
You worked so hard

724
00:38:25,836 --> 00:38:27,972
to make everyone in the street smile.

725
00:38:30,074 --> 00:38:31,608
I can tell how much

726
00:38:31,609 --> 00:38:33,744
you love this town.

727
00:38:35,246 --> 00:38:37,281
And that makes me so happy.

728
00:39:02,773 --> 00:39:04,175
What's wrong, Eito?

729
00:39:06,110 --> 00:39:07,812
Are you tired?

730
00:39:08,713 --> 00:39:11,582
Are you feeling okay physically?

731
00:39:12,717 --> 00:39:14,518
Yeah, I'm fine.

732
00:39:16,053 --> 00:39:17,088
Good.

733
00:39:43,381 --> 00:39:45,515
- A business trip overseas?
- Yeah.

734
00:39:45,516 --> 00:39:47,984
With President Neo and Tomono.

735
00:39:47,985 --> 00:39:50,687
Lucky you! Where are you going?

736
00:39:50,688 --> 00:39:52,189
- Paris, France.
- Oh!

737
00:39:53,524 --> 00:39:54,392
Paris?

738
00:39:55,393 --> 00:39:59,696
<i>Why is the current Kosei Neo
going to Paris</i>

739
00:39:59,697 --> 00:40:01,297
<i>when the Kosei Neo of that era</i>

740
00:40:01,298 --> 00:40:03,267
- <i>has never been there?</i>
- I'm going for work, Dad.

741
00:40:03,868 --> 00:40:06,736
We've been invited
to a concert at a theater.

742
00:40:06,737 --> 00:40:08,706
- A theater?
- A theater in Paris.

743
00:40:13,878 --> 00:40:15,745
- Sir.
- Yes?

744
00:40:15,746 --> 00:40:18,248
Pierre, the head of PR,
who had been unreachable

745
00:40:18,249 --> 00:40:19,817
since the France business trip…

746
00:40:21,552 --> 00:40:23,086
has been found dead.

747
00:40:23,087 --> 00:40:25,155
He appears to have been caught up

748
00:40:25,156 --> 00:40:27,924
in the simultaneous
Islamic extremist terrorist attacks

749
00:40:27,925 --> 00:40:29,326
at a Paris theater.

750
00:40:30,995 --> 00:40:33,397
So when is the trip?

751
00:40:34,031 --> 00:40:37,200
We arrive in Paris on November 13th

752
00:40:37,201 --> 00:40:38,435
and stay for three days.

753
00:40:38,436 --> 00:40:39,570
Wow!

754
00:40:40,271 --> 00:40:42,206
<i>November 13th…</i>

755
00:40:44,341 --> 00:40:46,544
<i>Isn't that the day of the Paris attacks?</i>

756
00:41:04,595 --> 00:41:07,531
Why is President Neo going to Paris?

757
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:10,500
To meet with President Nagamine

758
00:41:10,501 --> 00:41:14,004
of Kumamoto Scientific Industries,
the semiconductor manufacturer.

759
00:41:14,972 --> 00:41:18,108
He showed interest in your proposal.

760
00:41:19,009 --> 00:41:20,376
<i>In other words, my actions</i>

761
00:41:20,377 --> 00:41:22,612
<i>while living inside Eito</i>

762
00:41:22,613 --> 00:41:25,215
<i>have influenced and changed</i>

763
00:41:25,216 --> 00:41:28,385
<i>the history of the current Kosei Neo?</i>

764
00:41:29,119 --> 00:41:30,286
Why did Neo

765
00:41:30,287 --> 00:41:33,390
go along with your proposal? Well…

766
00:41:34,525 --> 00:41:36,893
because Soman's president, Ichimanda,

767
00:41:36,894 --> 00:41:39,663
was also targeting
Kumamoto's semiconductors.

768
00:41:40,464 --> 00:41:42,566
<i>Now that history has changed,</i>

769
00:41:43,267 --> 00:41:46,804
<i>Eri, Tomono, and Kosei Neo</i>

770
00:41:47,471 --> 00:41:50,040
<i>could all be caught up in the attack.</i>

771
00:41:51,108 --> 00:41:52,243
<i>On top of that,</i>

772
00:41:52,843 --> 00:41:56,247
<i>if Kosei Neo died,
what would happen to me?</i>

773
00:41:57,348 --> 00:41:58,883
With your influence,

774
00:42:00,317 --> 00:42:03,554
is there any way to stop the Paris trip?

775
00:42:04,355 --> 00:42:06,357
That came out of nowhere.

776
00:42:07,491 --> 00:42:10,494
The schedule was set to match
President Nagamine's availability.

777
00:42:16,734 --> 00:42:17,835
Even so,

778
00:42:18,369 --> 00:42:21,571
is there any way to bring
President Nagamine to Tokyo instead?

779
00:42:21,572 --> 00:42:22,805
Instead of Paris?

780
00:42:22,806 --> 00:42:25,276
The deal will go better
if it happens in Tokyo.

781
00:42:26,810 --> 00:42:28,579
Why do you think that?

782
00:42:31,482 --> 00:42:32,583
A hunch.

783
00:42:34,251 --> 00:42:36,086
That's not easy to arrange,

784
00:42:37,655 --> 00:42:39,823
but I'll see what I can do.

785
00:42:42,326 --> 00:42:43,427
Thank you.

786
00:42:45,563 --> 00:42:48,966
I want to test that hunch of yours.

787
00:42:54,572 --> 00:42:57,107
NOVEMBER 13TH, 2015

788
00:43:02,179 --> 00:43:03,547
<i>Togo…</i>

789
00:43:04,515 --> 00:43:06,717
<i>Why is no one picking up?</i>

790
00:43:09,620 --> 00:43:11,387
Hello? Brother! What is it?

791
00:43:11,388 --> 00:43:13,757
I'm on my way to the airport too.

792
00:43:15,092 --> 00:43:18,262
I'm heading to where you are.

793
00:43:19,296 --> 00:43:20,130
Why?

794
00:43:21,398 --> 00:43:23,434
I just…

795
00:43:25,970 --> 00:43:28,372
Anyway, could you come back for now?

796
00:43:28,973 --> 00:43:32,543
<i>Can't everyone just shift their schedules?</i>

797
00:43:33,477 --> 00:43:36,113
That's just not possible.

798
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:38,148
Anyway…

799
00:43:38,916 --> 00:43:40,784
I just have
a really bad feeling about this.

800
00:43:41,485 --> 00:43:43,686
I'm heading to the airport

801
00:43:43,687 --> 00:43:45,455
right now, so…

802
00:43:45,456 --> 00:43:48,224
I have to hang up, so I'm sorry.

803
00:43:48,225 --> 00:43:50,927
<i>You don't need to see me off. See you.</i>

804
00:43:50,928 --> 00:43:52,196
Hey, wait…

805
00:43:58,202 --> 00:43:59,136
President Neo.

806
00:44:03,140 --> 00:44:04,241
<i>This is bad.</i>

807
00:44:05,109 --> 00:44:08,112
<i>This situation is absolutely catastrophic.</i>

808
00:44:19,423 --> 00:44:22,225
<i>‎The plaintiff has filed a complaint.</i>

809
00:44:22,226 --> 00:44:22,892
‎NEXT EPISODE
‎AKARI SHOPPING STREET GOT SUED

810
00:44:22,893 --> 00:44:25,962
<i>‎He might have the ability
‎to predict the future.</i>

811
00:44:25,963 --> 00:44:29,332
<i>‎A favor from President Neo to me?</i>

812
00:44:29,333 --> 00:44:33,236
<i>‎No way… did I just fall in love
‎for the first time?</i>

813
00:44:33,237 --> 00:44:33,936
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION
‎MY FIRST LOVE BEGINS

814
00:44:33,937 --> 00:44:34,872
Subtitle translation by: Ken Nishizaki
